quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  29,53,"They challenge you ˹O Prophet˺ to hasten the punishment. Had it not been for a time already set, the punishment would have certainly come to them ˹at once˺. But it will definitely take them by surprise when they least expect it"
  29,54,They urge you to hasten the punishment. And Hell will certainly encompass the disbelievers
  29,55,"on the Day the punishment will overwhelm them from above them and from below their feet. And it will be said, “Reap what you sowed.”"
  29,56,"O My believing servants! My earth is truly spacious, so worship Me ˹alone˺"
  29,57,"Every soul will taste death, then to Us you will ˹all˺ be returned"
  29,58,"˹As for˺ those who believe and do good, We will certainly house them in ˹elevated˺ mansions in Paradise, under which rivers flow, to stay there forever. How excellent is the reward for those who work ˹righteousness!˺—"
  29,59,"those who patiently endure, and put their trust in their Lord"
  29,60,"How many are the creatures that cannot secure their provisions! ˹It is˺ God ˹Who˺ provides for them and you ˹as well˺. He is indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  29,61,"If you ask them ˹O Prophet˺ who created the heavens and the earth and subjected the sun and the moon ˹for your benefit˺, they will certainly say, “God!” How can they then be deluded ˹from the truth˺"
  29,62,God gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. Surely God has ˹full˺ knowledge of everything
  29,63,"And if you ask them who sends down rain from the sky, giving life to the earth after its death, they will surely say, “God!” Say, “Praise be to God!” In fact, most of them do not understand"